Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.32,0:00:10.91,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(400,400)}July 3rd, 1873 {慶応八年七月三日 - Keio era only lasted 3 years, but "Due to this, Honda had to create a worldview that made sense. He decided to have the game take place in an alternate version of the Edo Shogunate period where the Keiō era continued for a while, as he felt that it would be interesting if were set in the past rather than the future. The Keiō era was just before the Meiji Restoration, and he wanted to create a worldview that was, in his words, "like the evening of a festival"."}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.76,0:00:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ma, what that?{}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.53,0:00:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.26,0:01:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I have not a single idea where the key might be.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.96,0:01:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Achoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.25,0:01:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Not here! It's not here! \NDoesn't seem to be here. What about there, Pochi?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.42,0:01:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No...{no clue, I don't think it's a talking creature at all}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.90,0:01:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's very bad, so search over there too!\NIf we don't find it, no one gets their dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.78,0:01:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{see, I don't think it's talking}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.69,0:01:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.40,0:01:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.39,0:01:50.99,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,400)}Rami and Pochi present to you: \NKeio Flying Squadron - Action Movie Edition \NSpecial Original Video
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.32,0:01:55.89,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,600)}Half a year has passed since the ark catastrophe... {あの方舟騒動から半年...}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.40,0:01:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Greetings!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.33,0:01:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Kaian the Kappa here.{no clue, not in credits}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.16,0:02:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.75,0:02:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, I've been invited here to serve \Nas the presenter in charge of introducing this game. {}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.72,0:02:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's begin at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.04,0:02:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy who already made an appearance{no clue what's "did entry last time"}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.44,0:02:16.01,Top,,0,0,0,,is the ultra-intelligent tanuki \Nwith an IQ of 1400 points, Doctor Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.56,0:02:16.01,Sign,,0,0,70,,{\an2\fs50}Dr. Pon
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.17,0:02:19.67,Top,,0,0,0,,And here we can see, for the first time,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.67,0:02:23.62,Top,,0,0,0,,the fruits of Yamataikoku's labor \Nin the field of technology - Touma and Shima. {投馬 / 斯馬}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.18,0:02:23.14,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\an2\fs50}Touma
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.62,0:02:26.71,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\an2\fs50}Shima
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.94,0:02:31.20,Top,,0,0,0,,And with them, Yamataikoku's 19th Queen \NYamatai Himiko, on the quest to rebuild the kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.20,0:02:33.18,Sign,,0,0,90,,{\an2\fs50}Himiko {卑弥呼}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.73,0:02:37.45,Top,,0,0,0,,Facing them is Rami-chan, \Nwho manages to put up a fierce fight all by herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.59,0:02:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Having crossed the Chichibu range, she rows down \Nthe Sumida river, in Ryogoku today, in Kanda tomorrow! {no clue about anything before sumida}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.27,0:02:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Last time, we saw her riding Pochi's back, \Nnow it's Rami-chan's turn to shine once more!{not sure about a single word there, many are outright guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.66,0:02:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This time as well, she flies and she springs \Nand inevitably goes berserk wherever she comes! Yes, her! {no clue about anything but ooabare and kore ga}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.63,0:02:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to lay her own hands on the treasure,{doesn't make sense, she's supposed to be protecting it?;}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.84,0:02:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Rami-chan would go through fire and water.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.93,0:03:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, who would've thought she'd make it this far?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.01,0:03:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That said, her carefree lifestyle \Nmakes her put it off for later time after time...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.25,0:03:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But if she doesn't find the six jewels, \Nhidden throughout Japan
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.17,0:03:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and obtains the treasures of Yamataikoku,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.38,0:03:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,her carefree and easygoing luxurious life \Nthat she dreamt of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.71,0:03:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,will come to an abrupt end, \Nmuch like dreams always do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.73,0:03:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Always following in Rami-chan's shadow, \Nsupporting her - only Pochi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.94,0:03:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But this time around, \Nthey're joined by one more companion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.69,0:03:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Who is it, you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.96,0:03:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be me! Kaian the Kappa!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.45,0:03:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Depending on her attitude, I can send Rami-chan to various destinations that you wouldn't be able to access normally! {no clue what to make of "depending on the way of using"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.92,0:03:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, I'm such a reliable and nice guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.92,0:03:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor Pon's minions have gotten a little better \Nat what they're doing, {g}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.46,0:03:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but still can't handle her with their bare hands!{}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.33,0:03:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But hear me. Hear me, it's fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.62,0:04:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Rami-chan's power during the journey \Nis twice or thrice the power of their weapon!{}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.51,0:04:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Atami, Hinugawa, and Kusatsu remain hidden! {assuming he talks about jewels}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.31,0:04:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If you succeed collecting those, {nc}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.81,0:04:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody would be able to get the better of you!{}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.42,0:04:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, you'll get a massive stage \Nwith a chase through the space with the UFO Corps. {}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.25,0:04:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in this big three-sided struggle for Japan, {}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.59,0:04:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,would Doctor Pon's wisdom play the decisive role?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.18,0:04:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Or would it be Yamataikoku's technology, \Nwielded by Himiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.10,0:04:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Or perhaps, Rami-chan's drive, after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.50,0:04:39.16,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,500)}Then, what happened one night... {ある夜のできごと...}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.44,0:04:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Half a year has passed since the Ark Catastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.04,0:04:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The urban area of Edo gradually keeps recovering.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.73,0:04:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Of the traces left behind by that incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.17,0:04:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing remains, but the enormous crater, \Nsurrounding the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.06,0:05:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,In the process of restoration works, \Nat the site of the future Edo Castle basement, {}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.15,0:05:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,a mysterious discovery was made.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.77,0:05:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside a huge right arm, \Nwas hidden a transparent ball with a star inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.98,0:05:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And with it, an old scroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.33,0:05:40.57,Top,,0,0,0,,However, those suddenly disappeared \Non the very next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.57,0:05:42.50,Top,,0,0,0,,Together with Doctor Pon,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.50,0:05:47.38,Top,,0,0,0,,who happened to be working part-time \Nat that construction site to fund his activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.44,0:05:50.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\an2\fs20\pos(599,304)\fade(0,1500)}A bold crime! \NPart-time student \Ncharged with embezzlement {大胆!\Nアルバイト学生\N発掘物＊＊ - no clue what's last two charactes but don't care}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.30,0:05:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, several months later...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.15,0:06:03.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,500)}At that time at Nanahikari family... {そのころ七光家では...}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.93,0:06:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.09,0:06:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.95,0:06:32.27,Top,,0,0,0,,Sorry for interrupting your dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.95,0:06:34.46,Sign,,0,0,150,,{\an2\fs40}Queen of Yamataikoku\NHimiko the 13th {邪馬台国女王\N十三代目 卑弥呼}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.27,0:06:34.46,Top,,0,0,0,,I'm taking this with me. Bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.38,0:06:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! A jewel our ancestors \Npassed to us through generations!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.18,0:06:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you just staring?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.65,0:06:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Transform and chase after her at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.64,0:06:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Here! {}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.47,0:06:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Not you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.21,0:06:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.74,0:06:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Hyper Cutie Rami-chan Change!{}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.46,0:07:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.09,0:07:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.90,0:07:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.96,0:07:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.47,0:07:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? No way! I can't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.33,0:07:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Doctor Pon!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.00,0:07:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That is mine, so give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.33,0:07:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So sorry, but that's not happening. \NI'll give you something even better in return, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.84,0:07:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? What? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.71,0:07:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Merry Christmas!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.18,0:07:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.90,0:07:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, good. The angle is right. Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.69,0:07:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's going on? What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.11,0:07:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Please stop, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.43,0:07:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There are five other balls like that jewel, \Nbut of other colors.{}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.32,0:07:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If you collect them all, you get rewarded \Nwith a giant treasure, they say.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.21,0:08:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Rami! Go and collect all the jewels!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.71,0:08:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.81,0:08:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,For me!{}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.28,0:08:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.13,0:08:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, just kidding!{}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.67,0:08:16.56,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,500)}Fateful rival {宿命のライバル}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.78,0:08:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,At last, all six jewels are in my possession!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.46,0:08:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, I can revive the only one who can break the seal \Non this stupid enchanted door, the Mythical Giant{ Kappa}! {no clue what's kusakanjo}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.94,0:08:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, answer my call! Mythical Giant{ Kappa}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.24,0:08:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's good.{}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.71,0:08:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, open that gate, \Nbehind which the treasure is hidden!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.46,0:09:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It worked It worked!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.60,0:09:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the end, I'm the one to have the last laugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.67,0:09:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Too bad for you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.07,0:09:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's not happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.38,0:09:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.49,0:09:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The main heroine appears!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.64,0:09:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,500)}And the story comes to a shocking end... {そして物語は\N衝撃のラストへ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.70,0:09:35.00,Top,,0,0,0,,Pochi!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.00,0:09:36.60,Top,,0,0,0,,The star of the newly built Edo! {nc what's hananooedo}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.60,0:09:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Me - Rami, and my pet Pochi!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.52,0:09:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Again and again and again, \Nwe cause a huge commotion!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.34,0:09:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Exciting incident-filled journey in the Bakumatsu era, \NKeio Flying Squadron: Action Movie Edition!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.65,0:09:46.55,Sign,,0,0,0,,Saturn exclusive software\NKeio Flying Squadron - Action Movie Edition \NReleased on May 17, '96\NVictor Entertainment Co., Ltd. {サターン専用ソフト\N慶応遊撃隊 活劇編\N'96年5月17日発売 \Nビクターエンタテインメント株式会社}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.95,0:09:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now available on Saturn!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.55,0:09:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We've also launched a campaign! {}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.55,0:09:48.85,Sign,,0,0,0,,Battles with making a killing \NIncludes special goods present\NCampaign underway!\NFinal deadline: August 31, '96 (must be postmarked on that day)\NFor more details, please see the guidebook inside the product {just google translated, I don't care: 一獲千金大作戰之\N特製グッズプレゼント\Nキャンペーン実施中!\N最終締切: '96年8月31日 (当日消印有効)\N詳しくは商品内の案内書をご覧ください。}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.75,0:09:54.51,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(500,700)}Interview with creators \NDirector: Honda Akira{制作者インタビュー\N演出: 本田 暁}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.17,0:09:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing I wanted to do was...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.53,0:10:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Was this kinda peculiar character.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.21,0:10:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the industry is full with cute and strange characters. {}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.55,0:10:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So I wanted to imagine there's a world where they can coexist. {}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.01,0:10:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That kind of world, and on top of that, some kind of game.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.56,0:10:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we kinda wanted to create that kind of world, \Nwith a sense of unity.{}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.87,0:10:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, initially, well, that was kinda the general idea we had. {effectively everything he'll say is a guess, I won't be specifying it anymore, he's too fucking silent there}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.46,0:10:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So we wanted a story that was inspired \Nby the Kachi-Kachi Mountain folktale.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.80,0:10:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The result is then\Nsynthesized on top of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.33,0:10:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,[???]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.09,0:10:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The main character is Bunny Girl, well a rabbit, in fact. \NAlso inspired by the Kachi-Kachi Mountain folktale.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.59,0:10:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Both the rabbit and the tanuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.56,0:10:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just another kind of rabbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.95,0:10:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's how the rabbit came to be the main heroine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.98,0:10:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, we couldn't make it an actual rabbit, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.85,0:10:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And well, when I think about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.34,0:11:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,when I think of a rabbit, I think of a bunny girl. \NThat was the course my thoughts took.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.83,0:11:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But well, making her a usual bunny girl \Nwould be kinda trite too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.25,0:11:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, this kind of a big-breasted older sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.38,0:11:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, so, that was not the image I wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.43,0:11:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just... [???] How do I put it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.77,0:11:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We wanted her to look cool, a kinda gamer girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.09,0:11:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And well, that was a bit too...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.96,0:11:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That didn't match my vision for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.05,0:11:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we had to think of some other way...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.23,0:11:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So... She should be a bunny girl,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.53,0:11:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but well, without the usual protruding part here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.99,0:11:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Physically, she had to lose her sexiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.71,0:11:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, without [???]
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.94,0:11:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In short, it was the cutesy bunny girl image that we aimed for.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.83,0:11:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's also why she is so young. (12)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.38,0:11:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If she was to become the protagonist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.50,0:11:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just before Meiji Restoration,{subs from here on are from https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y42hsbC0S1U&ab_channel=Bragon%27salt - I don't care enough to translate inteviews myself}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.27,0:11:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so I wanted to create a worldview that is like
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.19,0:11:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the eve of a festival, where people\Nare cheering for a great cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.24,0:12:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I made a lot of adjustments, such as
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.41,0:12:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,picking fruits and vegetables, and\NI also made a lot of movements,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.14,0:12:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,like in shooting games, especially today's games.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.96,0:12:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You hit so many eggs and you hardly see
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.89,0:12:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the moment when the enemy character\Nappears, because you get hit right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.68,0:12:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried my best to draw, but I could\Nhardly get anyone to look at my work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.32,0:12:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In the second one, we're going to play a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.25,0:12:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,proper action game this time. \NAnd if we do that, the characters themselves will be a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.29,0:12:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,little questionable if we make it an action game,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.68,0:12:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And, as for dying soon, I would like to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.85,0:12:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,see the characters move and have fun with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.24,0:12:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The most difficult thing was the refugee's\Neastward progress, or the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.87,0:12:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Japan 3 The characters are drawn in the\Nsame gender to about the 4th grade, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.32,0:12:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more like the image of a researcher's
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.97,0:12:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,book on other animated films,\Nonly thinner and more conflicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.56,0:13:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They appear to almost\Ndisappear when viewed in game.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.88,0:13:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It depends on how many places you\Nare painting, and that's a bad idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.20,0:13:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I was told to lower the investment trust,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.60,0:13:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,For me, breathing and contraction\Nare not the same as language.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.08,0:13:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There was, but I kept it shrunk in a way
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.41,0:13:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was just so-so, and it was on my body.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.45,0:13:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, in the end, it made me feel
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.25,0:13:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that the original image remained pretty\Nmuch the same that way, on the contrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.44,0:13:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.04,0:13:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I had memories of the city as a whole, but
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.05,0:13:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the first time I've been\Nattached to the King's You for Table.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.16,0:13:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The second half came out in the shooter,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.24,0:14:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and as for that, I'm afraid you'll have\Nto see the extra section in the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.24,0:14:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Do a little bit of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.24,0:14:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that what you mean by that kind of "ah-ha"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.12,0:14:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There are UFOs and mysterious things, but
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.41,0:14:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,they are not the same\Nas what love follows.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.92,0:14:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem to be saying on a person level
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.25,0:14:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are quite in\Nlove with the character.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.32,0:14:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The first 1 in the second column. That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.92,0:14:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take the 1 of 2, your head will go all the way to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.60,0:14:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if you hang up on one,\Nyou can't make a phone call there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.15,0:14:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know about you, but the monkey\Nmode seems to be very easy this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.68,0:14:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Just in monkey mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.92,0:14:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many enemy characters that we
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.89,0:14:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot see, so if possible, we would like to see them in a single film.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.68,0:14:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It was amazing and balled up in a\Ncozy, flowery Asakusa-like setting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.24,0:14:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We made it like such a game so that people\Ncould play it in an amusement park.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.40,0:15:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be amazing if people\Ncould enjoy it like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.36,0:15:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, the leaving mode is much gentler.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.92,0:15:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope everyone will get into it and\Nwatch it through to the end if possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.90,0:15:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm told you'll get a treasure if you make it to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.07,0:15:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does it seems as though there won't be any end, then?!{not a single word lol}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.39,0:15:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Tamaki-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.62,0:15:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Keio Flying Squadron - Action Movie Edition \Nnow on sale for Saturn!
